== THE ESSENTIALS (Don't Leave Without These)

These items genuinely matter. Everything else is optional.

- _Insurance card and ID_ - You'll register upon arrival
- _Phone and charger_ (get a 10-foot cord - hospital outlets are always behind the bed)
- _Birth plan copies_ - Two or three printed copies for nurses and doctors
- _Going-home outfit for you_ - Something loose that fit when you were 5-6 months pregnant
- _Going-home outfit for baby_ - Weather-appropriate, 0-3 month size
- _Car seat_ - Properly installed before labor begins. Staff will check before discharge
- _Comfortable robe or cardigan_ - Hospital gowns open in the back
- _Slip-on shoes or slippers_ - You'll be walking the halls
- _Hair ties_ - Simple but essential during labor
- _Toiletries_ - Toothbrush, toothpaste, deodorant, face wash (hospital basics are very basic)
- _Glasses or contacts_ - If you need them
- _Nursing bra_ - If you're planning to breastfeed
- _Disposable underwear_ - Depends or similar (more on this below)
- _Snacks_ - A few granola bars, crackers, dried fruit

