== FOR LABOR

Labor can last hours or days. Pack items that help you cope with contractions and pass the time during early labor.

=== Comfort Items
- _Your own pillow_ - Hospital pillows are thin and plastic-covered. Bring one from home in a bright, non-white pillowcase so it doesn't get left behind
- _Fuzzy socks or gripper socks_ - Hospital floors are cold and slippery
- _Lightweight robe_ - Easier than hospital gowns when walking, especially if you want to cover up
- _Lip balm_ - Breathing techniques dry out your mouth
- _Hair ties and headbands_ - Keep hair off your face

=== Natural Pain Management
- _Massage oil or lotion_ - For back rubs during contractions
- _Tennis balls_ - For counter-pressure on your lower back
- _Heat pack_ (microwavable rice sock) - Hospital may have these, but bring your own to be safe
- _Comb_ - Squeezing a comb in your palm during contractions activates acupressure points

=== Food and Drinks
Check your hospital's policy first - some restrict eating during labor.

- _Clear liquids_ - Coconut water, sports drinks, broth packets
- _Sugar-free hard candy_ - Keeps your mouth moist without making you thirstier
- _Light snacks_ - Crackers, applesauce pouches, honey sticks for energy
- _Water bottle with a straw_ - Easier to drink while lying down

=== Entertainment for Early Labor
Early labor can take 12+ hours. You might be bored before you're uncomfortable.

- _Phone loaded with shows or podcasts_ - Download offline, hospital WiFi is unreliable
- _Book or magazine_ - Screen-free option
- _Headphones_ - For your own entertainment and for focus during active labor

=== The Big One
- _Extra-long phone charger_ - 10 feet minimum. Outlets in hospital rooms are always in the worst spots. You'll want your phone for timing contractions, music, and yes, those first photos.

