== FOR AFTER BIRTH

Recovery is messier than pregnancy books prepare you for. Pack accordingly.

=== Clothing
- _Going-home outfit_ - Loose dress or stretchy pants with an empire waist. Skip anything with a tight waistband. Your belly will still look 5-6 months pregnant.
- _Nursing bras or tanks_ - Soft, no underwire. Your breasts will be tender and changing size.
- _Comfy pajamas or nightgown_ - Optional. Hospital gowns work fine, but some people feel more human in their own clothes.
- _Cardigan or zip-up hoodie_ - Easy to nurse in and hospital rooms run cool

=== The Underwear Situation
The hospital provides mesh underwear and giant pads. They work. But many experienced moms swear by bringing their own Depends-style disposable underwear instead. Here's why:

_Depends (or similar) are better because:_
- Everything stays in place - no shifting pads
- You don't have to worry about leaks onto hospital bedding
- Easier to pull up and down when you're sore
- Feel more like actual underwear than mesh
- No bulky pad situation

Bring a pack in your hospital bag and a pack at home. You'll use them for 1-2 weeks postpartum.

=== Toiletries
Hospital toiletries are functional but not pleasant. Bring:
- _Your own shampoo and conditioner_ - Travel sizes work
- _Face wash and moisturizer_
- _Deodorant_
- _Toothbrush and toothpaste_
- _Makeup_ - Only if it makes you feel better. Most people skip it.

