== FOR BABY

This list is short because the hospital provides almost everything. Don't overpack baby items.

=== What You Actually Need to Bring
- _Going-home outfit_ - Weather-appropriate. In winter, choose something that works with a car seat harness (avoid puffy snowsuits). In summer, a lightweight cotton outfit with a hat for sun protection.
- _Receiving blanket_ - For the car seat in cold weather. Never put baby in a puffy coat in the car seat.
- _Car seat_ - Installed correctly in your vehicle BEFORE labor. This is non-negotiable. The hospital won't discharge you without a safe car seat. Get it checked at a local fire station or certified inspection site if you're not confident in the installation.

=== What You Don't Need to Bring
- Multiple outfits (baby will wear hospital blankets and a onesie)
- Diapers (hospital provides them)
- Wipes (hospital provides them)
- Pacifier (wait until breastfeeding is established, usually 3-4 weeks)
- Hats (hospital provides them)
- Socks and mittens (baby will be swaddled)

_One outfit. One blanket. Car seat. That's it._

