== NATURAL BIRTH ADD-ONS

Planning an unmedicated birth? These items help create a calm environment and provide natural pain relief.

=== Atmosphere
- _Battery-powered LED candles_ - Real flames aren't allowed. Warm white gives a calming glow.
- _Fairy lights_ - Battery-powered string lights can transform a clinical room
- _Bluetooth speaker_ - For hypnobirthing tracks, meditation, or calming music
- _Eye mask_ - For resting between contractions and blocking harsh hospital lighting
- _Focal point object_ - Something to focus on during contractions. A photo, a small statue, anything meaningful.

=== Scent
- _Essential oils_ - Check hospital policy first. If allowed:
  - Lavender for relaxation
  - Peppermint for nausea
  - Clary sage to support contractions (use only during active labor)
  - Frankincense for grounding
- _Diffuser_ - Portable battery-powered diffuser
- _Tissues or cotton balls_ - For placing essential oil drops if diffuser isn't allowed

=== Pain Management
- _TENS unit_ - Transcutaneous electrical nerve stimulation. The BabycareTENS brand has a specific "boost" mode for contractions. Place electrodes on lower back during early labor. Many people find significant relief from this.
- _Massage tools_ - Roller balls, wooden massage tools, anything that helps your partner apply counter-pressure without tiring out their hands
- _Birth ball_ - Hospital usually provides these, but confirm
- _Rice sock_ - Tube sock filled with rice, microwave to warm. Amazing for back labor.
- _Peanut ball_ - Helps open pelvis if laboring on your side

=== Mental Focus
- _Birth affirmation cards_ - Printed or on your phone
- _Hypnobirthing audio_ - Downloaded to your phone (don't rely on streaming)
- _Headphones_ - To listen without distraction
- _Printed birth preferences_ - Multiple copies

