== PRO TIPS

_Pack early._ 35-37 weeks. Babies arrive on their own schedule.

_Use separate bags._ One small bag for labor (things you'll want access to immediately), one bag for postpartum and baby stuff, partner has their own bag. Label them.

_Leave valuables home._ No expensive jewelry, no large amounts of cash. Hospital rooms have limited security.

_Wear your going-home outfit to the hospital._ It'll be loose and comfortable - perfect for laboring in at home before you head in. Then you have a real outfit to go home in and don't need to bring one.

_Preload your phone._ Download music, hypnobirthing tracks, shows, podcasts before you go. Hospital WiFi is notoriously unreliable.

_Bring an empty bag._ You'll accumulate hospital supplies, paperwork, and gifts. Having a collapsible bag to bring everything home is helpful.

_Know your hospital's specific policies._ Call ahead and ask:
- Can you eat during labor?
- Are essential oils/diffusers allowed?
- Do they provide birthing balls?
- What's the visitor policy?

_Pack snacks for after delivery._ Hospital kitchen may be closed when you deliver. Having crackers, nuts, or granola bars means you can eat when you're starving at 3am.

_Bring your own pillow._ Use a distinctive pillowcase so it doesn't get mixed up with hospital linens.

